sushi? Is it good?

514
00:18:40,420 --> 00:18:43,223
No, no. I didn't.
I'm a, I'm a vegan.

515
00:18:43,256 --> 00:18:43,890
Oh.

516
00:18:43,923 --> 00:18:45,225
Anyway.

517
00:18:45,258 --> 00:18:47,627
You might want to go easy
on the bubbles.

518
00:18:47,660 --> 00:18:50,263
Ah.

519
00:18:50,297 --> 00:18:51,331
(sighs)

520
00:18:51,364 --> 00:18:52,532
Smooth.

521
00:18:52,565 --> 00:18:53,800
Beginner's bad luck.

522
00:18:53,833 --> 00:18:55,902
Look, it's hard
to do justice

523
00:18:55,935 --> 00:18:57,804
to my captivating essence,
but she'll get the hang of it.

524
00:18:57,837 --> 00:19:00,473
Don't be such
a Debbie Downer, Daniel.

525
00:19:02,509 --> 00:19:05,144
(quietly):
Sorry.

526
00:19:09,616 --> 00:19:11,584
Hey.
Hey.

527
00:19:11,618 --> 00:19:12,919
Hi.

528
00:19:12,952 --> 00:19:14,254
You're really tan.

529
00:19:14,287 --> 00:19:15,888
Are you, uh, are you a surfer?

530
00:19:15,922 --> 00:19:18,391
Well, I'd sure like to surf
in your eyes.

531
00:19:18,425 --> 00:19:19,459
LUCIFER:
Ugh, dearie me.

532
00:19:19,492 --> 00:19:22,229
He's lucky it's not a crime
to be a cheeseball.

533
00:19:22,262 --> 00:19:23,796
Anyway, at least
the ice is broken.

534
00:19:23,830 --> 00:19:25,732
Now, just make small talk.

535
00:19:25,765 --> 00:19:28,568
So I drove up
to this meditation retreat

536
00:19:28,601 --> 00:19:30,270
in Big Sur last week.

537
00:19:30,303 --> 00:19:31,304
No, no, no!

538
00:19:31,338 --> 00:19:32,372
PCH is closed.

539
00:19:32,405 --> 00:19:33,473
Say you helicoptered...

540
00:19:33,506 --> 00:19:34,407
Shush.

541
00:19:34,441 --> 00:19:35,842
Uh, excuse me?

542
00:19:35,875 --> 00:19:37,944
Sploosh. I said "sploosh."

543
00:19:37,977 --> 00:19:39,946
Are you into splooshing?

544
00:19:56,596 --> 00:19:57,764
(sighs)

545
00:19:57,797 --> 00:20:00,767
Time to change tactics.

546
00:20:00,800 --> 00:20:02,435
You know what?

547
00:20:03,903 --> 00:20:06,205
Enjoy the Prosecco, Lucinda.

548
00:20:08,475 --> 00:20:09,976
I don't believe this.

549
00:20:10,009 --> 00:20:11,878
Ditching protocol mid-sting?

550
00:20:11,911 --> 00:20:13,313
Who does that?

551
00:20:13,346 --> 00:20:15,582
Maybe she'll do better
on her own.

552
00:20:15,615 --> 00:20:16,549
Don't be ridiculous, Daniel.

553
00:20:16,583 --> 00:20:18,718
She'll flounder
without my expert guidance.

554
00:20:18,751 --> 00:20:19,852
Oh, yeah.
Right.

555
00:20:19,886 --> 00:20:21,521
I'm clearly needed
on the front lines.

556
00:20:21,554 --> 00:20:23,756
You just stay here
and do what you do best.

557
00:20:25,358 --> 00:20:26,526
Nada.

558
00:20:26,559 --> 00:20:28,361
(scoffs)

559
00:20:31,364 --> 00:20:32,699
CHLOE:
Oh, I love traveling.

560
00:20:32,732 --> 00:20:33,800
Oh, yeah?
Yeah.

561
00:20:33,833 --> 00:20:34,901
Any fun plans coming up?

562
00:20:34,934 --> 00:20:37,537
Um, well, I...

563
00:20:37,570 --> 00:20:40,407
I was thinking of, uh,
maybe getting out of the city

564
00:20:40,440 --> 00:20:42,709
and taking my
daughter camping.

565
00:20:42,742 --> 00:20:43,810
Cool.

566
00:20:43,843 --> 00:20:45,678
I-I love the outdoors.

567
00:20:45,712 --> 00:20:46,813
CHLOE: Oh.
I'm a surfer.

568
00:20:46,846 --> 00:20:48,615
CHLOE:
Really?

569
00:20:48,648 --> 00:20:49,882
Goes well with camping.

570
00:20:49,916 --> 00:20:51,784
I've always wanted
to try surfing.

571
00:20:51,818 --> 00:20:52,919
But I...
You should...

572
00:20:53,820 --> 00:20:54,921
Oh, hi, Lucifer.

573
00:20:54,954 --> 00:20:56,389
This is Benji.

574
00:20:56,923 --> 00:20:57,724
CHLOE:
He just had

575
00:20:57,757 --> 00:20:59,025
four pieces of sashimi,

576
00:20:59,058 --> 00:21:00,793
and we just started
talking about surfing.

577
00:21:00,827 --> 00:21:02,495
Oh, lovely. Now, I insist

578
00:21:02,529 --> 00:21:03,963
you put your mic back in
immediately.

579
00:21:03,996 --> 00:21:05,498
We can't hear a thing
in the truck.

580
00:21:05,532 --> 00:21:07,033
You are being quite loud.

581
00:21:07,066 --> 00:21:08,968
(groans)
Nice work.

582
00:21:09,869 --> 00:21:11,838
LUCIFER:
Bloody hell.

583
00:21:11,871 --> 00:21:13,039
WOMAN:
Hey, there goes Benji!

584
00:21:13,072 --> 00:21:15,542
MAN:
Benji, over here!

585
00:21:15,575 --> 00:21:17,510
Whoa.
You have to save me from them.

586
00:21:17,544 --> 00:21:18,778
DAN:
Uh, yeah.

587
00:21:18,811 --> 00:21:20,947
They're with me.

588
00:21:20,980 --> 00:21:22,649
Not bad for nada, huh?

589
00:21:22,682 --> 00:21:23,750
(chuckles)

590
00:21:23,783 --> 00:21:24,784
Wait, she's a cop?

591
00:21:24,817 --> 00:21:26,052
Detective Decker, LAPD.

592
00:21:26,085 --> 00:21:27,920
We want to talk to you
about a murder.

593
00:21:27,954 --> 00:21:29,656
MAN:
Benji, you're the best, bro!

594
00:21:29,689 --> 00:21:30,823
You're not paparazzi?

595
00:21:30,857 --> 00:21:32,525
What?

596
00:21:32,559 --> 00:21:33,426
Oh, thank God.

597
00:21:33,460 --> 00:21:36,429
I mean, the things
Dad gets credit for.

598
00:21:36,463 --> 00:21:37,430
(mouths)

599
00:21:41,501 --> 00:21:43,636
Yeah, I went on a date with her.

600
00:21:43,670 --> 00:21:45,938
Just the other night.

601
00:21:45,972 --> 00:21:48,841
Still can't believe she's, uh...
she's dead.

602
00:21:48,875 --> 00:21:50,410
Oh?

603
00:21:50,443 --> 00:21:52,745
Did you think she'd survive
you murdering her?

604
00:21:52,779 --> 00:21:54,681
I told you, I'm innocent.

605
00:21:54,714 --> 00:21:55,915
Well, you're an overpaid DJ,

606
00:21:55,948 --> 00:21:57,650
so that's up for debate.

607
00:21:57,684 --> 00:22:00,553
It seems you were the last
person to see Kim alive.

608
00:22:00,587 --> 00:22:01,921
I couldn't have been.

609
00:22:01,954 --> 00:22:03,456
When I dropped her off
after our date,

610
00:22:03,490 --> 00:22:04,657
her roommate was still there.

611
00:22:04,691 --> 00:22:05,692
How do you know that?

612
00:22:05,725 --> 00:22:07,560
Because that's the reason
I didn't go upstairs

613
00:22:07,594 --> 00:22:08,961
like Kim suggested.

614
00:22:08,995 --> 00:22:10,129
I was trying to avoid Esther.

615
00:22:10,162 --> 00:22:11,864
What, kombucha martini girl?

616
00:22:11,898 --> 00:22:13,666
Do you know her roommate?

617
00:22:13,700 --> 00:22:15,568
To the extent
that you can know someone

618
00:22:15,602 --> 00:22:17,670
who's glued to her phone
and talks in hashtags.

619
00:22:17,704 --> 00:22:18,905
(scoffs)
Yep, that's her.

620
00:22:18,938 --> 00:22:20,407
How did you two meet?

621
00:22:20,440 --> 00:22:23,710
We matched on the Top Meet app
a few weeks ago.

622
00:22:23,743 --> 00:22:25,011
Went on two exhausting dates.

623
00:22:25,044 --> 00:22:27,947
Then why go on the second date?

624
00:22:27,980 --> 00:22:29,582
Because I wanted
to see Kim again.

625
00:22:29,616 --> 00:22:32,151
I met her at the apartment
when I picked up Esther

626
00:22:32,184 --> 00:22:33,986
for our first date.

627
00:22:34,020 --> 00:22:36,155
She wasn't there
the second time.

628
00:22:36,188 --> 00:22:38,157
So you can imagine
how stoked I was

629
00:22:38,190 --> 00:22:39,826
when she popped up
on the Top Meet app.

630
00:22:39,859 --> 00:22:40,827
LUCIFER:
No.

631
00:22:40,860 --> 00:22:42,028
I can't, actually.

632
00:22:42,061 --> 00:22:44,163
You're saying that you used
a top hat to get to a shoe?

633
00:22:44,196 --> 00:22:45,965
He must be lying, Detective.

634
00:22:45,998 --> 00:22:47,166
BENJI:
I'm not lying.

635
00:22:47,199 --> 00:22:49,469
I really liked Kim.

636
00:22:49,502 --> 00:22:52,071
She was different than all
the other women on the app.

637
00:22:52,104 --> 00:22:53,506
What, different as in duller,

638
00:22:53,540 --> 00:22:55,174
more mundane
and dressed for less?

639
00:22:55,207 --> 00:22:57,510
No, as in she
didn't make me feel

640
00:22:57,544 --> 00:22:59,979
like I had to be on
all the time.

641
00:23:00,012 --> 00:23:03,149
With her, I could...

642
00:23:03,182 --> 00:23:05,084
I could just be myself.

643
00:23:06,118 --> 00:23:07,420
Interesting.

644
00:23:09,221 --> 00:23:10,389
Thanks.

645
00:23:11,758 --> 00:23:12,659
(clears throat)

646
00:23:12,692 --> 00:23:15,562
What if Esther found out
about Benji and Kim?

647
00:23:15,595 --> 00:23:16,963
Got jealous,
lost control...

648
00:23:19,499 --> 00:23:22,569
This goddess,
jealous of the plain Jane?

649
00:23:22,602 --> 00:23:23,770
It's-it's ludicrous!

650
00:23:23,803 --> 00:23:25,905
It's like me being jealous
of that paper clip.

651
00:23:25,938 --> 00:23:26,973
Or Daniel.

652
00:23:27,006 --> 00:23:29,108
I mean, not to mention

653
00:23:29,141 --> 00:23:32,178
Esther is far too busy
for murder, Detective.

654
00:23:32,211 --> 00:23:34,046
Look. She flew
to Florence last week

655
00:23:34,080 --> 00:23:35,515
just 'cause she fancied
eating some gelato.

656
00:23:35,548 --> 00:23:37,083
She went on a plane
to get ice cream?

657
00:23:37,116 --> 00:23:39,486
Well, when you say it in
English, it sounds silly.

658
00:23:39,519 --> 00:23:41,954
Oh. Hello.
Look at that belfie.

659
00:23:41,988 --> 00:23:44,824
(chuckles) Bet you could bounce
a quarter off that derrière.

660
00:23:46,559 --> 00:23:47,994
Oh. Yeah...

661
00:23:49,161 --> 00:23:50,763
Wait, uh, go back.

662
00:23:50,797 --> 00:23:52,532
There.
What?

663
00:23:52,565 --> 00:23:54,801
Something small and compact

664
00:23:54,834 --> 00:23:56,135
and surprisingly heavy
for its size.

665
00:23:56,168 --> 00:23:57,937
Well, what's Miss Lopez's
Aunt Rosalita

666
00:23:57,970 --> 00:23:59,438
got to do with anything?

667
00:24:00,740 --> 00:24:01,708
Look.

668
00:24:01,741 --> 00:24:02,942
The dumbbell.

669
00:24:02,975 --> 00:24:04,110
It wasn't at the crime scene.

670
00:24:04,143 --> 00:24:06,078
It matches the bruises
on the victim,

671
00:24:06,112 --> 00:24:07,013
it's a weapon
of convenience,

672
00:24:07,046 --> 00:24:09,148
and it fits the crime of passion
scenario.

673
00:24:09,181 --> 00:24:11,784
Doesn't mean Esther was
the one to wield it, though.

674
00:24:11,818 --> 00:24:13,920
If my theory of jealousy
is right, she was.

675
00:24:13,953 --> 00:24:15,755
Trust me, Detective,

676
00:24:15,788 --> 00:24:17,990
there's no way that Esther
has ever used a weight--

677
00:24:18,024 --> 00:24:20,493
I refer once again to her
naturally sublime derrière.

678
00:24:29,268 --> 00:24:31,671
(quietly):
Oh, crap.

679
00:24:45,618 --> 00:24:47,854
You're avoiding me, aren't you?

680
00:24:47,887 --> 00:24:49,789
Don't be crazy.

681
00:24:49,822 --> 00:24:51,591
No. I just...

682
00:24:51,624 --> 00:24:54,894
you know,
like my floors spotless.

683
00:24:54,927 --> 00:24:58,164
An evidence lab can
never be too clean.

684
00:24:58,197 --> 00:25:02,802
And that is your Forensic
Lesson of the Day.

685
00:25:02,835 --> 00:25:03,936
More next week?

686
00:25:03,970 --> 00:25:05,838
Why don't you want to mentor me?

687
00:25:05,872 --> 00:25:08,641
It's not that
I don't want to, okay?

688
00:25:08,675 --> 00:25:09,876
I just don't have the time.

689
00:25:09,909 --> 00:25:11,110
Well, I've been watching you.

690
00:25:11,143 --> 00:25:12,111
You have plenty of time.

691
00:25:12,144 --> 00:25:13,946
You just waste it chitchatting.

692
00:25:13,980 --> 00:25:15,615
You mean socializing?

693
00:25:15,648 --> 00:25:18,885
Connecting with people
isn't a waste.

694
00:25:18,918 --> 00:25:20,319
Okay.

695
00:25:20,352 --> 00:25:23,623
Let's be honest here.

696
00:25:23,656 --> 00:25:27,326
You don't really care about
anyone's kids or whatever.

697
00:25:27,359 --> 00:25:29,629
I mean, you're faking it, right?

698
00:25:29,662 --> 00:25:32,732
Just tell me, how do you keep
your eyes from glazing over?

699
00:25:34,266 --> 00:25:36,603
There is no Forensic Shadow
Program, is there?

700
00:25:37,870 --> 00:25:41,307
Even if I had been
tempted to help--

701
00:25:41,340 --> 00:25:44,043
and I'm not saying
that I had--

702
00:25:44,076 --> 00:25:45,812
now that I know you lied?

703
00:25:45,845 --> 00:25:47,346
Poof!

704
00:25:47,379 --> 00:25:50,817
Temptation officially gone.

705
00:25:53,820 --> 00:25:54,887
* All right

706
00:25:57,757 --> 00:26:00,126
* She said the ride is rough

707
00:26:00,159 --> 00:26:04,196
* But love the way it rumbles

708
00:26:04,230 --> 00:26:05,297
* Mmm

709
00:26:05,331 --> 00:26:06,899
* She said
the ride is rough... *

710
00:26:06,933 --> 00:26:10,069
Okay, so I'm thinking:
big band over here

711
00:26:10,102 --> 00:26:13,940
and two long, two long
buffet tables over here...

712
00:26:13,973 --> 00:26:15,241
or should we do three?

713
00:26:15,274 --> 00:26:17,076
Well, it depends. How
many people are coming?

714
00:26:17,109 --> 00:26:18,745
Uh, just 350.

715
00:26:18,778 --> 00:26:20,947
350?

716
00:26:20,980 --> 00:26:22,114
Wow.

717
00:26:22,148 --> 00:26:24,751
I didn't realize how much
you still cared about Reese.

718
00:26:24,784 --> 00:26:25,451
Of course I do!

719
00:26:25,484 --> 00:26:27,253
I'm heartbroken about his death.

720
00:26:27,286 --> 00:26:29,121
Distraught, really.

721
00:26:29,155 --> 00:26:30,690
Can barely function.

722
00:26:31,958 --> 00:26:33,926
Okay, okay.

723
00:26:33,960 --> 00:26:37,630
Okay, okay, okay, okay,
I'm functioning perfectly.

724
00:26:37,664 --> 00:26:38,765
I only feel terrible

725
00:26:38,798 --> 00:26:40,800
that I don't feel terrible
about his death.

726
00:26:40,833 --> 00:26:42,902
Okay, so all of this
is just a...

727
00:26:42,935 --> 00:26:44,771
A pathetic attempt
to cover up the fact

728
00:26:44,804 --> 00:26:49,408
that I can't stop thinking
about me.

729
00:26:49,441 --> 00:26:51,711
Me, me.

730
00:26:51,744 --> 00:26:53,813
Me and my own brush with death.

731
00:26:53,846 --> 00:26:55,982
I understand, Linda. I mean...
How could you
possibly understand

732
00:26:56,015 --> 00:26:57,850
what it's like to be rotisseried

733
00:26:57,884 --> 00:27:00,286
by the, by the goddess
of all creation?

734
00:27:02,288 --> 00:27:04,423
Dealing with mortality
was so much easier

735
00:27:04,456 --> 00:27:07,626
when I was just another
clueless idiot.

736
00:27:08,961 --> 00:27:13,299
Being a celestial insider...
really sucks.

737
00:27:13,332 --> 00:27:15,234
I used to walk
around thinking

738
00:27:15,267 --> 00:27:18,437
maybe reincarnation was real.

739
00:27:18,470 --> 00:27:20,907
Sure, it sounded bonkers,

740
00:27:20,940 --> 00:27:25,344
but I could still wonder,
still hope.

741
00:27:27,146 --> 00:27:30,016
What if I came back
as a chameleon or something?

742
00:27:31,918 --> 00:27:33,319
Chameleons are cool.

743
00:27:35,321 --> 00:27:37,356
But now I know
that's never happening,

744
00:27:37,389 --> 00:27:41,427
because I know,
you know, everything,

745
00:27:41,460 --> 00:27:45,031
including where I'm headed
when... when this is over.

746
00:27:45,064 --> 00:27:46,332
And where is that?

747
00:27:46,365 --> 00:27:47,834
Where do you think?

748
00:27:49,769 --> 00:27:52,238
I wish I'd never met any of you.

749
00:27:59,912 --> 00:28:03,750
CHLOE: So we wanted
to, uh, ask you

750
00:28:03,783 --> 00:28:04,917
a few...

751
00:28:04,951 --> 00:28:06,853
Would you want
to put on a shirt,

752
00:28:06,886 --> 00:28:09,856
or anything to cover...
your body?

753
00:28:09,889 --> 00:28:12,391
No. Why? Are you cold?

754
00:28:12,424 --> 00:28:14,060
Yes. Would you like
my jacket, Detective?

755
00:28:14,093 --> 00:28:15,461
No. I am great, thank you.

756
00:28:15,494 --> 00:28:16,863
Right.

757
00:28:16,896 --> 00:28:20,066
So, when was this photo taken?

758
00:28:20,099 --> 00:28:25,872
Uh, I took that on my way
to Tokyo, I think.

759
00:28:25,905 --> 00:28:27,239
Sorry.

760
00:28:27,273 --> 00:28:29,241
I travel so much,
it's hard to keep track.

761
00:28:29,275 --> 00:28:30,209
(laughs)

762
00:28:30,242 --> 00:28:31,477
It's actually
something else

763
00:28:31,510 --> 00:28:32,979
that we're trying to track down.

764
00:28:33,012 --> 00:28:34,213
This pink dumbbell here?

765
00:28:34,246 --> 00:28:36,015
It went missing
the night of Kim's murder.

766
00:28:36,048 --> 00:28:37,316
Any idea where it went?

767
00:28:37,349 --> 00:28:38,117
Nope.

768
00:28:38,150 --> 00:28:40,452
It's not mine.
I don't work out.

769
00:28:40,486 --> 00:28:42,221
Ah.
Everything you see

770
00:28:42,254 --> 00:28:44,056
is God-given.
LUCIFER:
And they say that

771
00:28:44,090 --> 00:28:45,792
Dad doesn't give
with both hands.

772
00:28:45,825 --> 00:28:46,893
So, the dumbbell.

773
00:28:46,926 --> 00:28:47,994
You're saying that's Kim's?

774
00:28:48,027 --> 00:28:49,228
Yeah. Poor thing

