(Lucifer chuckles)

1029
00:38:30,542 --> 00:38:31,943
*

1030
00:38:31,977 --> 00:38:34,045
LUCIFER:
But in the end,

1031
00:38:34,079 --> 00:38:35,847
the shoe turned out
to be interesting,

1032
00:38:35,881 --> 00:38:37,816
and the top hat, boring.

1033
00:38:37,849 --> 00:38:42,521
Right. So you're gonna
embrace your boring side now?

1034
00:38:42,554 --> 00:38:44,122
Well, I would,
but I have no boring side.

1035
00:38:44,155 --> 00:38:46,892
Ah.
Even the most trivial
of nights takes a turn

1036
00:38:46,925 --> 00:38:48,560
for the exciting
when I'm involved.

1037
00:38:48,594 --> 00:38:50,729
I just got to throw
a man's own head at him.

1038
00:38:50,762 --> 00:38:54,065
That sounds... painful.

1039
00:38:54,099 --> 00:38:56,368
Oh, don't worry,
he deserved it--

1040
00:38:56,402 --> 00:38:58,570
for pretending to be
something he wasn't.

1041
00:38:58,604 --> 00:39:01,106
I mean, people really do waste
an awful lot of time

1042
00:39:01,139 --> 00:39:03,842
trying to be interesting.

1043
00:39:03,875 --> 00:39:04,976
People.

1044
00:39:05,010 --> 00:39:06,378
Not you, though.

1045
00:39:06,412 --> 00:39:08,480
Oh, no. To me,
it just comes effortlessly.

1046
00:39:08,514 --> 00:39:11,717
All I have to do
is just be myself.

1047
00:39:11,750 --> 00:39:12,651
Hmm.

1048
00:39:12,684 --> 00:39:13,485
Mm.

1049
00:39:13,519 --> 00:39:16,121
But what I really want
to know is,

1050
00:39:16,154 --> 00:39:18,056
how have you been doing?

1051
00:39:20,726 --> 00:39:23,061
Well...

1052
00:39:23,094 --> 00:39:25,664
I was in a really dark place.

1053
00:39:27,499 --> 00:39:28,333
But...

1054
00:39:28,366 --> 00:39:32,438
someone helped me
gain perspective.

1055
00:39:32,471 --> 00:39:35,774
How's that saying go?

1056
00:39:35,807 --> 00:39:37,609
We're all in the gutter,

1057
00:39:37,643 --> 00:39:40,045
but some of us are
looking up at the stars.

1058
00:39:40,078 --> 00:39:41,012
The stars are just gas bags,

1059
00:39:41,046 --> 00:39:42,948
and I never would have
fed Oscar that line

1060
00:39:42,981 --> 00:39:46,184
had I known how much I'd have to
hear people quote it back to me.

1061
00:39:46,217 --> 00:39:47,886
Oscar freakin' Wilde?

1062
00:39:47,919 --> 00:39:49,621
Mm-hmm.
Really?

1063
00:39:49,655 --> 00:39:51,857
Now, he was
an interesting bachelor.

1064
00:39:51,890 --> 00:39:52,891
(chuckles)

1065
00:39:52,924 --> 00:39:55,527
Anyway, I'm glad to hear
that you are doing better.

1066
00:39:55,561 --> 00:39:57,496
This calls
for a celebration.

1067
00:39:57,529 --> 00:40:00,131
So...

1068
00:40:00,165 --> 00:40:02,634
Oscar, huh?

1069
00:40:02,668 --> 00:40:03,502
Mm.

1070
00:40:03,535 --> 00:40:05,637
Tell me everything.
(sighs):
Well...

1071
00:40:05,671 --> 00:40:08,540
he was straight
when I first met him.

1072
00:40:11,943 --> 00:40:13,411
(gasps):
Oh, God!

1073
00:40:14,946 --> 00:40:16,081
That one was all you.

1074
00:40:16,114 --> 00:40:17,683
I was about to knock.

1075
00:40:19,585 --> 00:40:22,821
(sighs): There's...
something I need to tell you.

1076
00:40:22,854 --> 00:40:24,556
Funny.

1077
00:40:24,590 --> 00:40:27,826
There's actually something
I need to tell you, too.

1078
00:40:29,595 --> 00:40:30,562
Thank you.

1079
00:40:30,596 --> 00:40:33,932
That contract helped put
a killer behind bars.

1080
00:40:33,965 --> 00:40:35,701
You did a good thing.

1081
00:40:35,734 --> 00:40:37,035
I stole it.

1082
00:40:37,068 --> 00:40:38,537
Aw, man.

1083
00:40:38,570 --> 00:40:40,038
Seriously?

1084
00:40:41,206 --> 00:40:42,508
You know what?

1085
00:40:42,541 --> 00:40:44,042
It still counts, okay?

1086
00:40:44,075 --> 00:40:46,478
You did a bad thing.

1087
00:40:46,512 --> 00:40:49,915
But it was for
a good reason.

1088
00:40:49,948 --> 00:40:51,182
Really?
Yes.

1089
00:40:51,216 --> 00:40:53,184
But only if,
in good faith,

1090
00:40:53,218 --> 00:40:55,554
you try to do it
the right way first.

1091
00:40:55,587 --> 00:40:57,923
Being good
takes practice.

1092
00:40:57,956 --> 00:41:00,091
Okay? So just keep at it,

1093
00:41:00,125 --> 00:41:02,494
and you'll get better.

1094
00:41:02,528 --> 00:41:05,997
I guess I should take
that job, then.

1095
00:41:06,031 --> 00:41:07,766
What job?

1096
00:41:07,799 --> 00:41:11,737
I've been offered a position
in the D.A.'s office to...

1097
00:41:11,770 --> 00:41:14,606
help put criminals away
for a change.

1098
00:41:14,640 --> 00:41:16,975
Yeah, but like you would
ever take that pay cut.

1099
00:41:17,008 --> 00:41:19,110
Yeah, I know.

1100
00:41:19,144 --> 00:41:20,078
(sighs):
But anyway,

1101
00:41:20,111 --> 00:41:22,881
um, sometimes there's
more important things...

1102
00:41:22,914 --> 00:41:24,282
than money.

1103
00:41:24,315 --> 00:41:28,186
Oh, yeah. Yeah, like
all the things money can buy.

1104
00:41:28,219 --> 00:41:31,122
Too late--
you talked me into it.

1105
00:41:31,156 --> 00:41:32,524
I did?

1106
00:41:32,558 --> 00:41:36,094
Yes. This job is
the perfect place...

1107
00:41:36,127 --> 00:41:38,697
to practice
this "being good" thing.

1108
00:41:38,730 --> 00:41:39,798
And bonus.

1109
00:41:41,032 --> 00:41:42,901
I'll be around here more.

1110
00:41:44,002 --> 00:41:45,804
(chuckles quietly)

1111
00:41:45,837 --> 00:41:47,873
Yeah.

1112
00:41:47,906 --> 00:41:49,708
Bonus.

1113
00:41:51,943 --> 00:41:55,080
So, how did
Lucinda do, Mom?

1114
00:41:55,113 --> 00:41:57,315
Uh, she did... okay.

1115
00:41:57,348 --> 00:42:00,185
Helped us catch the
bad guy in the end.

1116
00:42:00,218 --> 00:42:02,253
Thank you.
No, I meant...

1117
00:42:02,287 --> 00:42:04,823
how did meeting new people
at the party go?

1118
00:42:04,856 --> 00:42:06,925
Oh.

1119
00:42:06,958 --> 00:42:08,326
Well, um...

1120
00:42:08,359 --> 00:42:11,997
I actually...
had a pretty good time.

1121
00:42:12,030 --> 00:42:15,300
I mean, but only once I...
stopped being Lucinda

1122
00:42:15,333 --> 00:42:17,736
and started being myself.

1123
00:42:20,038 --> 00:42:23,742
You know, it can be scary
sometimes, but...

1124
00:42:23,775 --> 00:42:27,312
being who you really are
is never a bad idea.

1125
00:42:27,345 --> 00:42:29,848
Hey, there's a piece missing.

1126
00:42:31,683 --> 00:42:34,185
(mellow jazz piano playing)

1127
00:42:34,219 --> 00:42:36,822
*

1128
00:42:43,128 --> 00:42:45,096
Lucifer.

1129
00:42:45,130 --> 00:42:46,732
(exhales)

1130
00:42:46,765 --> 00:42:47,933
Are you coming?

1131
00:42:47,966 --> 00:42:49,067
Uh...

1132
00:42:49,100 --> 00:42:51,970
how about a nice
round of Monopoly?

1133
00:42:52,003 --> 00:42:53,204
Yeah?

1134
00:42:53,238 --> 00:42:55,206
Little face-
painting, maybe?

1135
00:42:55,240 --> 00:42:57,308
(chuckles)

1136
00:42:57,342 --> 00:42:59,745
I didn't think so.

1137
00:43:00,178 --> 00:43:01,880
Hmm.

1138
00:43:01,913 --> 00:43:03,849
*

